{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01LgVTctXQakLLjzG5SDJGoH","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I understand the setup:\n1. MinIO credentials: user=`minioadmin`, password=`minioadmin`\n2. Elasticsearch is version 8.11.1 with xpack security enabled\n3. The secret `es-secure-settings` doesn't exist yet - I need to create it\n\nThe task requires:\n- Configure secure settings so Elasticsearch can authenticate to MinIO\n- The credentials should NOT be in elasticsearch.yml or env vars\n- They should be in the Elasticsearch keystore via the `es-secure-settings` Secret\n\nFor Elasticsearch 8.x with the S3 repository plugin (or in this case, we need to check if the S3 plugin is installed since MinIO is S3-compatible), the keystore-based approach is:\nI need to create the `es-secure-settings` Secret with MinIO credentials as keystore entries, then mount it in the Elasticsearch pods so they can be loaded into the keystore. Since there's no Elasticsearch operator managing this StatefulSet, I'll need to either mount the secret as a file and load it manually, or use an init container to populate the keystore with the S3 client credentials.\n\nLet me check what plugins are already installed in the Elasticsearch pods to see what's available.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":440,"cache_read_input_tokens":32043,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":440},"output_tokens":23,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"2fcdfef7-30f2-4e5b-9b00-102e91aa0193","uuid":"52a7533c-c355-4cd9-9f99-9ddb9f877333","request_id":"req_011Cc929ChYKXdrPQeJTiK8V"}
