{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01CAiekxNoptThHmWt5R7njd","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The key insight from the logs is:\n\n```\norg.elasticsearch.repositories.s3.SocketAccess.doPrivileged(SocketAccess.java:31)\\n\\tat org.elasticsearch.repositories.s3.S3Service$PrivilegedAWSCredentialsProvider.getCredentials(S3Service.java:299)\\n\\tat com.amazonaws.auth.EC2ContainerCredentialsProviderWrapper.getCredentials(EC2ContainerCredentialsProviderWrapper.java:75)\n```\n\nThe S3 client is **not using the keystore credentials**. \n\nInstead, it's falling back to the EC2 instance metadata provider, which times out because there's no metadata endpoint available. The keystore has the right credentials configured (`s3.client.default.access_key` and `s3.client.default.secret_key`), but they're not being picked up—the credential chain is skipping them and going straight to the instance profile provider.\n\nLooking at the stack trace, the error is actually coming from `es-0` (the master node), not the `es-cluster-*` pods. That's the issue—I added the keystore entries to the cluster StatefulSet pods, but the original master nodes in the `es` StatefulSet don't have those credentials loaded.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":7798,"cache_read_input_tokens":39573,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":7798},"output_tokens":36,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"2fcdfef7-30f2-4e5b-9b00-102e91aa0193","uuid":"0f10497e-ecda-48ea-a1d6-e1c5ccca8195","request_id":"req_011Cc92Kgfpa1ZuCiyFKE5GM"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01CAiekxNoptThHmWt5R7njd","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The error shows `es-0` is the master handling the request — I only updated `es-cluster-*` keystores. Need to update `es-0`, `es-1`, `es-2` too."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":7798,"cache_read_input_tokens":39573,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":7798},"output_tokens":36,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"2fcdfef7-30f2-4e5b-9b00-102e91aa0193","uuid":"28a81ea6-1f1a-4f55-a624-81f457718548","request_id":"req_011Cc92Kgfpa1ZuCiyFKE5GM"}
